Angry pensioners of defunct Nigeria Airways yesterday evening (about 6.02 pm) blocked Minister of finance, Hajiya Zainab Ahmed from leaving the premises. The protesting pensioners, in their handful number, claimed they travelled to Abuja from various parts of the country on the invitation of the ministry for data capturing. Some of them who spoke to New Telegraph lamented the hardship they were subjected since on Sunday as they had to sleep in open space within and around finance ministry premises. The Minister, who was rushing home to break her Ramadan fast after a meeting with Heads of agencies under her ministry was caught in web of protest. The protesters barricaded the entrance to the main gate. Details laterâ€¦